## Overview

This roadmap integrates the **Board-Centric UI Architecture** from `cardplay/cardplayui.md` with the vision of a configurable board system for any type of userâ€”from notation composers to graphic composers to tracker users to sound designersâ€”with "as much or as little AI as you want."

The AI system will be **Prolog-based** (rule-based reasoning, not neural networks) using declarative logic over deck layouts, music theory, and compositional patterns. Reference implementation: https://github.com/kkty/prolog

### Roadmap Structure

The roadmap is organized into **logical phases** that build upon each other:

1. **Phase A: Baseline & Repo Health** (A001â€“A100) - Fix type errors, stabilize APIs, establish baseline
2. **Phase B: Board System Core** (B001â€“B150) - Core board types, registry, persistence, validation
3. **Phase C: Board Switching UI & Persistence** (C001â€“C100) - Board switcher, browser, first-run flow
4. **Phase D: Card Availability & Tool Gating** (D001â€“D080) - Runtime gating logic, tool visibility
5. **Phase E: Deck/Stack/Panel Unification** (E001â€“E090) - Deck instances, factories, drag/drop
6. **Phase F: Manual Boards** (F001â€“F120) - Pure manual boards (notation, tracker, sampler, session)
7. **Phase G: Assisted Boards** (G001â€“G120) - Manual + hints/phrases (tracker+harmony, etc.)
8. **Phase H: Generative Boards** (H001â€“H075) - AI-driven boards (arranger, composer, ambient)
9. **Phase I: Hybrid Boards** (I001â€“I075) - Power user boards (composer, producer, live performance)
10. **Phase J: Routing, Theming, Shortcuts** (J001â€“J060) - Visual polish, routing overlay, shortcuts
11. **Phase K: QA, Performance, Docs, Release** (K001â€“K030) - Final QA, benchmarks, release prep
12. **Phase L: Prolog AI Foundation** (L001â€“L400) - Prolog engine, knowledge bases, query system
13. **Phase M: Persona-Specific Enhancements** (M001â€“M400) - Deep persona workflows
14. **Phase N: Advanced AI Features** (N001â€“N400) - Learning, adaptation, advanced inference
15. **Phase O: Community & Ecosystem** (O001â€“O400) - Templates, marketplace, collaboration
16. **Phase P: Polish & Launch** (P001â€“P200) - Final polish, documentation, launch prep

**Total Steps: ~2,800** (expandable as needed)

